# Changelog

All notable changes to TubeGrab will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [1.0.0] - 2024-02-11

### Added
- Initial release of TubeGrab
- Video download functionality with quality selection
  - Best Quality (highest available)
  - 1080p Full HD
  - 720p HD
  - 480p SD
  - 360p Low
  - Custom format selection
- MP3 audio extraction with bitrate options
  - 320 kbps (Best)
  - 256 kbps (High)
  - 192 kbps (Medium)
  - 128 kbps (Standard)
  - 96 kbps (Low)
- Colorful terminal user interface
  - Gradient banner
  - Color-coded menus
  - Status indicators
  - Progress messages
- Automatic dependency installation
  - yt-dlp auto-install
  - ffmpeg auto-install
  - Python auto-install
- Storage permission handling
- Video information display before download
- Format listing and selection guide
- Update checker for yt-dlp
- Comprehensive documentation
  - README.md with installation guide
  - USAGE.md with detailed instructions
  - QUICKSTART.md for fast setup
  - CONTRIBUTING.md for contributors
  - GitHub workflow for CI/CD
- MIT License
- .gitignore for clean repository
- Auto-installer script (install.sh)
- SVG banner for GitHub repository

### Features
- Works on all Android devices with Termux
- Downloads saved to phone's Download folder
- Smart file merging (video + audio)
- Multiple format support (MP4, WEBM, etc.)
- Error handling and user feedback
- Clean and intuitive menu system

### Technical
- Bash script compatible with Termux
- Uses yt-dlp for video/audio processing
- Uses ffmpeg for format conversion
- ANSI color support for beautiful UI
- Modular function design
- Error checking and validation

---

## [Unreleased]

